full_text:
On my way back to Canada after 3 days of meetings with #G7 leaders in Biarritz, France. Here‚Äôs what we worked on:
‚úîÔ∏èFighting climate change
‚úîÔ∏èCreating jobs & opportunities for the middle class
‚úîÔ∏èAdvancing gender equality
Read more: https://t.co/7GSoOHB3wB

Just over a month after the Canada-EU Summit in Montreal, @eucopresident and I caught up at the #G7 about the progress we've made on building a stronger Canada-EU partnership and increasing trade to create good jobs & more opportunities for people on both sides of the Atlantic. https://t.co/ZZUnOVXKJa

Had a good meeting with @ScottMorrisonMP at the #G7. We talked about issues that are important to Canadians and Australians: fighting climate change, regional cooperation, and creating economic opportunities for people in both our countries. https://t.co/mNeJT7ExGy

President @CyrilRamaphosa and I spoke at the #G7 about the strong relationship and common values shared by Canada and South Africa, like our commitment to democracy, girls' education, and economic growth that benefits everyone. Thanks for the meeting today, Cyril. https://t.co/4esMkaLJoL

Climate change is a global crisis, and we need to come together to fight it. Today‚Äôs working session at the #G7Biarritz focused on how we‚Äôre going to protect more land & waters, reduce plastic waste, and build a cleaner planet for everyone. https://t.co/Spm7e1ILx8

We cannot stand by and do nothing while our planet burns. Canada is stepping up with our G7 partners to #ActForTheAmazon by offering water bombers to fight the fires and funding for emergency response & reforestation. https://t.co/to3Tf7j0xz

With climate change, the global economy, and peace & security on the agenda, #G7Biarritz is tackling some of the world‚Äôs biggest challenges. Earlier today, @EmmanuelMacron & I met to talk about the progress we‚Äôre making and the strong Canada-France partnership. https://t.co/At3VelaIOM

Spent some time catching up with Chancellor Merkel this afternoon and talked about the need for international cooperation for peace & security, and to fight climate change & the fires in the Amazon. Nice to see you, my friend. https://t.co/fCi7gJTwDB

This afternoon at the #G7, I met with @PaulKagame to discuss the economic ties between Canada & Rwanda, the importance of free trade in Africa and the work we're doing as members of the Commonwealth and la Francophonie. https://t.co/9ps6guQyBC

None of us can move forward when half of us are held back. Last year we launched the Gender Equality Advisory Council under Canada's #G7 Presidency, and members are sharing their expertise again this year. Thanks for your recommendations on how we can #MakeGenderInequalityHistory https://t.co/w6iAc5XGbx

When everyone has a fair chance at success, all of society benefits. We had a working session today at the #G7 to talk about how we‚Äôre going to fight inequality around the world and ensure women & girls have equal rights and opportunities. https://t.co/pk8DDQuw6K

Canada and the US are close partners, and we‚Äôll keep working together to strengthen our relationship & create jobs for Canadians and Americans. @POTUS Donald Trump and I had a productive meeting today at the #G7. More on what we talked about here: https://t.co/tdXhvr72pN https://t.co/T0qLaM1hup
Day 2 of the #G7: discussing the global economy, promoting peace & security, and addressing inequalities to create more opportunity for the middle class. https://t.co/YVJWSJzEAs

My focus at the #G7 is working with our allies to strengthen the middle class - not just in Canada but around the world as well. We just wrapped up a productive first day in France, tackling some of the world‚Äôs biggest challenges. More to come tomorrow. https://t.co/55pIiguuNO

Always great to see you, @AbeShinzo. Glad we could talk at the #G7 about how we‚Äôll strengthen the relationship between our countries, fight climate change, address the fires in the Amazon & grow our trade partnership through the CPTPP to create opportunities for the middle class. https://t.co/L1KBt8QpS7

The UK is one of Canada‚Äôs closest friends ‚Äî we‚Äôre united by a long history & shared values. @BorisJohnson and I met at the #G7 today where we discussed strengthening trade between our countries and committed to address climate change, #ActForTheAmazon, & peace around the world. https://t.co/PhRgbRrLbi
Slava Ukraini! Today, we join Ukrainian communities in Canada and around the world to celebrate the 28th anniversary of Ukraine‚Äôs independence: https://t.co/t3BxFBA4Vx

We‚Äôre close to ending the HIV, TB & malaria epidemics for good. But we still need to do more, and Canada is committed to #StepUpTheFight to help @GlobalFund save lives. Melinda, thanks for your leadership on this issue and everything you do to help women & girls around the world. https://t.co/Ei4mqvDvhC

full_text: I spoke to @ZelenskyyUa yesterday ahead of the #G7. Get the details on our call: https://t.co/IfN4Fk9w7Z

We‚Äôve been focused on making life more affordable for Canadians, and one of the first things we did as a government was cut taxes for the middle class. That means 9 million Canadians now have more money in their pockets to help with the cost of living. https://t.co/8Xn7Tkq4sQ

Tomorrow, the #G7 countries will meet in France. And my message will be clear: As allies and world leaders, we need to work together in order to build a future where everyone can succeed. https://t.co/G6HKlUvOp9
Today on Black Ribbon Day, we join people around the world to pay tribute to the survivors and victims of Communism and Nazism in Europe: https://t.co/R0spBkPFrp

We're on our way to Biarritz, France for the #G7, where we‚Äôll be focused on creating more jobs & opportunities for people, and the steps we can take now to fight the climate crisis. https://t.co/5Zm1seHHjo

I couldn‚Äôt agree more, @EmmanuelMacron. We did lots of work to protect the environment at the #G7 last year in Charlevoix, & we need to continue this weekend. We need to #ActForTheAmazon & act for our planet ‚Äî our kids & grandkids are counting on us. https://t.co/KwaR8Eevq5

full_text: I sat down with Mayor @Val_Plante in Montreal today. Thank you, Val√©rie, for the productive conversation about how we‚Äôll keep working together to create jobs for Montrealers, fight climate change, and invest in the infrastructure this city needs. https://t.co/IDxAH3fXTM
LIVE now ‚Äì I‚Äôm speaking at @corim_mcfr about Canada‚Äôs role on the global stage, and how we‚Äôre working with our allies to build a better world: https://t.co/eZiqSJS4no

Visited the March√© Public in Sainte-Hyacinthe with @Rene_Vincelette today - families have been coming here for generations to shop & catch up with neighbours. We spoke to a few of them about their priorities & the future of this vibrant community. https://t.co/RlCtmaxw2I

.@NathRochefort is a longtime community leader who's passionate about helping people in her riding succeed. We grabbed some pastries and shared some laughs with families at Caf√©-Boulangerie Galato in Nicolet this morning. https://t.co/kOr1X8vPhi

We have a busy day ahead meeting people all over Quebec - first stop was breakfast with @ValRenaudMartin in Trois-Rivi√®res. Families here can count on Val√©rie to work hard to grow the middle class & make life more affordable. https://t.co/3KZUcuWlmY

Families have been shopping for their fruits, veggies, & more at the Marche Public in Sainte-Foy for over 40 years. @JoelLightbound and I spent some time today talking to the local producers here ‚Äì thanks for the warm welcome! https://t.co/BER6EQJ5IF

Had a good meeting with Mayor Labeaume in Quebec City today, focused on how we‚Äôll keep working together to build a stronger economy, create jobs, protect the environment, and invest to make life easier for families ‚Äì like the important tramway project we announced today. https://t.co/bI45YLE8yf

Big news in Quebec City today! We‚Äôre investing in public transit to help people get around the city faster, so they can spend less time on the road and more time with their families. Learn more: https://t.co/Bn4qgcwwYe https://t.co/PF9s1165BQ

Our government knows that supporting our unions leads to more jobs for Canadians & a stronger middle class. Together with @UniforCanada, we‚Äôll keep defending workers' rights, helping their families, & respecting the important work they do. Thanks for having me at #Unifor19 today. https://t.co/3TDo9FJMl0
Our government will always support Canada‚Äôs workers. Watch my speech at @UniforTheUnion‚Äôs Convention in Quebec City : https://t.co/EidmP5SG3B

Every day, humanitarian aid workers around the world make a lasting impact in the lives of millions of people. On #WorldHumanitarianDay, we pay tribute to their important work and recognize the sacrifices they make to help communities in crisis. https://t.co/5gRlxBKyFv
Today, we join Afghans and the Afghan-Canadian community in celebrating one hundred years of Afghanistan's Independence: https://t.co/g7rOxqdFvM

On this day in 1942, nearly 5,000 Canadians fought with courage and resilience in the Dieppe Raid. Their heroism changed the course of history, and their sacrifices will never be forgotten. #LestWeForget https://t.co/ppZTmPGKXb
Pride is about so much more than a parade. It‚Äôs about celebrating our differences, and supporting one another no matter whom we love. #loveislove #prideMTL https://t.co/eI7PsV51y2

I‚Äôll be in Biarritz, France from August 24-26 for the #G7 Leaders‚Äô Summit. Now more than ever, G7 leaders need to come together to fight the climate crisis, grow the middle class, & create opportunities for people around the world. https://t.co/iwxx4CTJ7w

full_text: I spoke with @POTUS Trump today. Read about our call here: https://t.co/ql9CDAlhCK

Stopped in Elmsdale today to catch up with Kody Blois, a hardworking community leader who‚Äôs been focused on helping people ‚Äì especially young people ‚Äì in his home riding of Kings‚ÄìHants. Thanks to Kody and the folks at @TheCupofSoul for the great conversations. https://t.co/Qx1IMc1ill

Our government introduced the First-Time Home Buyer Incentive to help with your down payment, lower your monthly mortgage & make it more affordable to buy a home. That‚Äôs great news for Canadians like Ryan & Victoria, who are looking to buy a place where little Hayden can grow up. https://t.co/UgrzKjWyWG

Organizations like @Techsploration in Nova Scotia are doing great work to support young women in science, the trades, and tech. We had a good discussion at @NSCCNews in Dartmouth today about how we can work together to keep opening doors for young women in these fields. https://t.co/GfaSQJDahf
Couldn‚Äôt leave New Brunswick without catching up with @DLeBlancNB. Good to see you, my friend (I think you were telling me a joke in this pic). https://t.co/PBv6kN4Jhj
Friends, music, food, and Le Grand Tintamarre ‚Äì that‚Äôs how you celebrate National Acadian Day. We had a blast in Dieppe today! https://t.co/NVVqDPzmqT
Acadians sure know how to throw a party and make some noise ‚Äì and they have a lot to celebrate at the 25th Congr√®s mondial acadien. #CMA2019 https://t.co/5nHJ5sYA5H

Acadians across the Maritimes ‚Äì and around the world ‚Äì are celebrating their beautiful language, music and culture today. Had a great time joining in with folks in Rogersville, NB. Vive l‚ÄôAcadie! https://t.co/XTIM5PyGnR
Lunch time at Parker‚Äôs Country Diner in Doaktown, NB: good conversations, great people, and even a few high fives! https://t.co/tUPUGnmyXP

With 3 major floods over the past 11 years, people in Fredericton and the surrounding area have faced the impacts & costs of the climate crisis first hand. Today we're stepping up with new funding to protect this community from future flooding. Read more: https://t.co/jlJSPk2TwM https://t.co/00k3Dwetaa
